The Managing Director of the Bank of Agriculture, Alwan Ali-Hassan was on Wednesday set free by terrorists who attacked a Kaduna-bound train after his family paid N100 million as ransom, SaharaReporters has gathered. Ali-Hassan and others were abducted last Monday, March 28 by terrorists who bombed the Kaduna-bound train carrying over 362 passengers.  Eight people were confirmed killed and 26 others injured in the attack. The Nigerian Railway Corporation (NRC) while confirming the incident, said about 362 passengers were on board the ill-fated train. According to the NRC, while about 182 have safely reunited with their families, about 162 other passengers remain missing. 



